    "what_description": "Kirkia leandrii is a species of plant in the family Kirkiaceae, native to Madagascar. It is a deciduous tree with a straight bole and a rounded crown, growing up to 20 meters in height. The leaves are alternate, simple, and elliptical, measuring 7-14 centimeters in length and 2-5 centimeters in width, with a ciliate margin. The flowers are greenish-yellow, hermaphroditic, and clustered, appearing in axillary racemes, with 5-6 petals and a 5-merous calyx. The fruit is a capsule, 5-7 centimeters in length, containing 2-4 seeds.",
